<br>
I KNOW there may not be a GM around, and that a petition might not be answered, but petitioning is important to do. Please see below.<br>
=============================================<br>
Unfortunately, this is most often men hassling women, so forgive me gents if this stuff feels uncomfortable.<br>
=============================================<br>
The policy:<br>
No harassment will be tolerated. If someone has a complaint, an officer will contact both of those involved and any witnesses also. This discussion will NOT be public. If there is legitimate evidence of harassment, and the officers feel it has been proven to their satisfaction, the harassing person will be deguilded, and the officers will decide if the information will be transmitted to a GM for Verant to consider barring the user from EQ.<br>
=============================================<br>
<br>
Now this is HARSHLY worded on purpose. But note that harassment has to be proven to the officers satisfaction, whatever that might be. Also, the level of response depends on the officers choice, either guild level or game level.<br>
<br>
=============================================<br>
Now, as to member suggestions -<br>
<br>
If you feel that you are being harassed:<br>
1 TELL them you don't like it. &quot;STOP THAT!&quot; or &quot;I don't like it when you talk to me that way.&quot;<br>
2 turn /log ON to document future stuff said or in tells. (I know they can always respond you altered the log, but at least it is there.) You might want to consider asking someone else who is with you to log things too, as an unbiased witness.<br>
3 TELL them you are logging anything they might say, emote or send in tells.<br>
4 TELL them you will make a complaint if they continue.<br>
5 Ask in /guildchat if there is an IAO on, or any OFFICER online NOW.<br>
5 Scroll up to display what they said, and use /REPORT to send it to the GMs.<br>
6 Send a /PETITION to the GMs and ask them to review the report you just made regarding being harassed. Ask the GM to send a tell to that officer you found on at the time, telling the officer you found above that a LEGITIMATE episode of harassment has occurred.<br>
7 TELL the harasser that you have done this, and that OBJECTIVE evidence has been sent to the GM and to guild officers. (This avoids he said/she said situations.)<br>
8 GO somewhere populated, so /say and emotes can be seen by others. This might help a little bit.<br>
9 USE /ignore XXXX so at least you won't even SEE any tells they might send to you. This sure can help.<br>
<br>
I know this is NOT perfect by any means. Please let me hear your comments...<br>
